A 52-year- old suspected fraudster Tayo Ogunmola is presently cooling his heels at the detention cell of the Ogun state police command for attempting to swindle the commandâ€™s Commissioner of Police, CP Bashir Makama. Police source said the suspect had called on phone pretending to be an old herbalist who mistakenly sent a recharge card pin to the telephone number of the CP therefore pleading for the pin to be sent back to him. It was gathered that since the CP who has been familiar with the antics of the fraudsters decided to play along with him while he sent men of the Intelligence Response Team, IRT, to technically track and apprehend the suspect. Our source said at a stage, the suspect who was not aware that he was being trailed was presenting himself to the CP as a Deputy Inspector General of Police who is ready to assist the CP only if he can part with certain amount of money unknown to him the person he has been discussing with is a serving commissioner of police. Ogun State Police Command image maker DSP Abimbola Oyeyemi, who confirmed the story to Daily Independent said luck however ran against him when he was traced to his hideout at Araromi phase 2, in ilogbo area of Ota where he was promptly arrested. On interrogation, he confessed being a fraudster who had defrauded many unsuspecting members of the public of money which runs to millions of naira out of which he built the house which he is living in presently. Meanwhile, the commissioner of police CP Bashir Makama has ordered the monitoring team to properly investigate the suspect with the view of arresting his other accomplices and arraign them before the court of competent jurisdiction.